# Code Conventions — PHP / Laravel

## General
- PHP 8.1+ — use typed properties, enums, match expressions, readonly where appropriate
- Strict types on every file: `declare(strict_types=1);`
- Follow PSR-12 coding standard
- Keep methods small and single-purpose
- Avoid magic — prefer explicit over clever

## Naming
- Controllers: `PascalCase`, singular, suffixed (e.g. `UserController`)
- Models: `PascalCase`, singular (e.g. `User`, `BusListing`)
- Migrations: `snake_case` with timestamp prefix (Laravel default)
- Routes: `kebab-case` (e.g. `/bus-listings/{id}`)
- Blade templates: `kebab-case` (e.g. `bus-listing-card.blade.php`)
- Jobs / Events / Listeners: `PascalCase` with descriptive suffix (e.g. `SendWelcomeEmail`)
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`

## File & Folder Structure (Laravel conventions)
```
app/
├── Http/
│   ├── Controllers/      # Thin controllers — delegate to services
│   ├── Middleware/
│   ├── Requests/         # Form Request validation classes
│   └── Resources/        # API Resources (JSON transformers)
├── Models/               # Eloquent models
├── Services/             # Business logic layer
├── Repositories/         # DB query abstraction (if used)
├── Jobs/                 # Queued jobs
├── Events/ + Listeners/
└── Enums/                # PHP 8.1 enums

resources/
├── views/                # Blade templates
└── js/ + css/            # Frontend assets

routes/
├── web.php
├── api.php
└── console.php
```

## Controllers
- Thin controllers — no business logic inside
- Delegate to Service classes
- Use Form Requests for validation
- Use API Resources for response transformation

## Models
- Define `$fillable` or `$guarded` explicitly
- Use relationships instead of raw queries where possible
- Scope complex queries into named scopes
- Never put business logic in models

## API Responses
Return consistent shapes via API Resources:
```php
return response()->json([
    'success' => true,
    'data'    => new UserResource($user),
    'message' => 'User retrieved successfully',
]);
```

## Database
- Always use migrations — never modify DB schema manually
- Use seeders for dev/test data
- Index foreign keys and frequently queried columns
- Use `unsignedBigInteger` for foreign keys

## Validation
- Always use Form Request classes for validation
- Never validate inside controllers directly
- Return 422 with structured error messages

## Imports / Namespaces
- Use full namespaces, not aliases unless standard (e.g. `Carbon`)
- Group use statements: 1) PHP built-ins, 2) Laravel, 3) App classes
